# 
categ_vars = [ele for ele in att_df.columns if type(att_df[ele].loc[0]) == type('is string')]
# Dummy Variables
att_df_dummy = pd.get_dummies(att_df, columns=categ_vars, drop_first=True, dtype=int)

XGBoost scikit-learn 

#  y  x
y = att_df_dummy['Attrition_Yes']  # 
x = att_df_dummy[np.setdiff1d(att_df_dummy.columns, ['Attrition_Yes']).tolist()]  # 
#  XGBoost 
import xgboost as xgb
mdl = xgb.XGBClassifier(n_estimators=20)  #  20
mdl.fit(x, y)  #

# classification
expl = dalex.Explainer(model=mdl, data=x, y=y, model_type='classification')
expl.model_diagnostics()  # 

#  SHAPSHapley Additive exPlanations
shap_result = expl.predict_parts(x.iloc[[0]], type='shap', B=10, random_state=0).result

#  DataFrame SHAP 
shap_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['name', 'value', 'mean'])
# 
x_vars = np.unique(shap_result['variable_name'])
#  SHAP 
for j in range(len(x_vars)):
    tmp = deepcopy(shap_result.loc[shap_result['variable_name'] == x_vars[j],])  # 
    scores = tmp.loc[tmp['B'] > 0, 'contribution'].values  #  B > 0 
    x_value = tmp.loc[tmp['B'] == 0, 'variable_value'].values[0]  # 
    shap_df.loc[j] = [x_vars[j], x_value] + [np.mean(scores)]  #  DataFrame

#  SHAP 
shap_df['abs_mean'] = np.abs(shap_df['mean'])  # 
shap_df.sort_values('abs_mean', ascending=False, inplace=True, ignore_index=True)  # 
shap_df.replace(np.nan, None, inplace=True)  #  None
print(shap_df)
